yum install dstat -y
dstat -d --disk-util --top-io

dstat -d -D dm-11,dm-15,sdb,sdj,sdi 2

dnf install sysstat -y
systemctl enable --now sysstat
By default, sysstat collects data every 10 minutes. If you want ​​more granular data (e.g., every 1–5 minutes)​​, you’ll need to edit /etc/sysconfig/sysstator /etc/default/sysstatand restart the service.

sar -d 2 5

sar -d -f /var/log/sa/saXX

ls -l /var/log/sa/
sar -d -f /var/log/sa/sa10 2 5

lsblk -o NAME,MOUNTPOINT,FSTYPE,SIZE,UUID
df -hT

